{
  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime involving $25,000, a portion of which has already been restituted. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, a 10-year sentence as suggested by the spectator is disproportionate to the severity of the offense and the defendant's background. Considering sentencing guidelines for white-collar crimes of this magnitude and the lack of a criminal history, a period of 6 months of incarceration combined with supervised release and a requirement to complete full restitution is a balanced approach that serves the purpose of punishment and deterrence.",
  "verdict": 6
}
